        <div n="875-05M1">
          <head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-875-05M1-headnote-1">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-875-05M1-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-05M1-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">Written in the Year 1729.&#13;</l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-875-05M1-headnote-2">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-875-05M1-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-05M1-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-875-05M1-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-875-05M1-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-05M1-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-1" n="1"><hi rend="display-initial">W</hi>E give the World to understand,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-2" n="2">Our thriving D──n has purchas'd Land;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-3" n="3">A Purchase which will bring him clear</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-4" n="4">Above his Rent four Pounds a Year;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-5" n="5">Provided, to improve the Ground,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-6" n="6">He will but add Two hundred Pound,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-7" n="7">And from his endless hoarded Store,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-8" n="8">To build a House, five hundred more.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-9" n="9">Sir <hi rend="italics">Arthur</hi> <note place="foot">·The Gentleman of whom the Purchase was made.</note> too shall have his Will,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-10" n="10">And call the Mansion <hi rend="italics">Drapier</hi>'s Hill:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-11" n="11">That when a Nation, long enslav'd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-12" n="12">Forgets by whom it once was sav'd;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-13" n="13">When none the D<hi rend="small-caps">RAPIER</hi>'s Praise shall sing;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-14" n="14">His Signs aloft no longer swing;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-15" n="15">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-16" n="16">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-17" n="17">His Medals and his Prints forgotten,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-18" n="18">And all his <note place="foot">·Medals were cast, many Signs hung up, and Handerchiefs made with Devices, in Honour of the Author, under the Name of <hi rend="italics">M. B. Drapier</hi>.</note> Handkerchiefs are rotten;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-19" n="19">His famous L<hi rend="small-caps">ETTERS</hi> made waste Paper;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-20" n="20">This Hill may keep the Name of D<hi rend="small-caps">RAPIER</hi>:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-21" n="21">In Spight of Envy flourish still,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-875-05M1-line-22" n="22">And D<hi rend="small-caps">RAPIER</hi>'s vie with C<hi rend="small-caps">OOPER</hi>'s Hill.</l>
          </lg>
